msItem.title: Dalāʼil al-khayrāt wa-shawāriq al-anwār fī dhikr al-ṣalawāt ʻalá al-Nabī al-mukhtār

supportDesc.extent: 88, i leaves; 160 x 115 (124 x78) mm bound to 160 x 125 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Maghribī in black ink, pointed; vocalized in red.

decoNote: Rubrications in red, green, yellow; illuminated text dividers (f. 1v, 30v, 48r, 64r, 69v, 88v); illustration of the Prophet's mosque at Medina (f. 13v); marginal medallions in black with red and yellow; textblock border-ruled in double red.

decoNote.@n: Inside back cover [flap open to show design]

locus.#text: Inside back cover [flap open to show design]

binding.p: Red leather with fore-edge flap (Type II); blind-tooled with two inset rectangles with double lines connecting the corners, matching tooling on flap with floral inlay, now missing; printed marbled paper doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed in A.H. 1185 (1771 or 1772 CE) (f. [88]v), probably in North Africa; a.H. 1185 (1771 or 1772 CE)

history.provenance: Gift of Mrs. William Furness Jenks, March 16, 1921; note in pencil "Jenks--Algiers 1876-77" (back flyleaf verso).
